<context>
	<score>0.7095387</score>
	<text>The class was withdrawn between 1961 and 1967 .</text>
</context>
<context>
	<score>0.6474535</score>
	<text>38 (46465 to 46502) were built at Darlington and allocated to the Eastern and North Eastern regions. The final 25 (46503 to 46527) were built at Swindon and, being allocated to the Western Region , consequently carried the GWR-type vacuum ejector and firehole doors. The Swindon locomotives were turned out, initially, in lined black. Under the Hanks regime, some received lined green livery as they passed through works. The rest carried black livery. None of the Class was named in service, however some have been named in preservation.</text>
</context>
